<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAY 93 / Construction Contracts: Evered Bardon awarded Pounds 17m for
US projects
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
EVERED BARDON, the international quarry and aggregates group, has won a
series of contracts in the US with a combined value of Dollars 27m (Pounds
17m).
In Massachusetts, Bardon Trimount will be the main contractor on four
highway resurfacing contracts valued at more than Dollars 16m. Over 300,000
tons of coated stone will be supplied to these contracts, which include
resurfacing a tolled section of Interstate 90 between Grafton and Framingham
for the Massachusetts Turnpike Authority.
The company has also won contracts to supply materials to two major projects
in downtown Boston. 17,000 cubic yards of readymix concrete will be supplied
to Turner Construction, which has won the contract to build the New England
Medical Centre, and more than 400,000 tons of aggregates are to be supplied
to Spectacle Island, part of the Dollars 6bn Boston Harbour clean-up scheme.
In Washington DC and Maryland, Evered Bardon's Mid-Atlantic division has won
contracts to supply more than Dollars 6m of materials. Over 300,000 tons of
aggregates will be supplied to the Government Federal Triangle building in
Washington DC and a similar quantity is to be railed and barged to the
Patuxent Naval Air Station in southern Maryland for a major resurfacing
contract.
The company has also been awarded the contract to supply 20,000 cubic yards
of readymix concrete to the Baltimore City Jail Annexe. Construction begins
this month. Aggregates for the concrete on this project will be supplied via
Evered Bardon's second aggregates rail terminal in the region, which opened
late last month at Canton in Baltimore City.
</TEXT>
