FT  10 MAY 93 / Fimbra suspends Scottish group
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A Scottish estate agency's investment business has been suspended by Fimbra,
the self-regulatory organisation, after it failed to notify the organisation
of a proposed change of name from Aberdeen Estate Agency to Dinnington.
It also failed to deal with Fimbra in 'an open and co-operative manner' in
not replying to letters.
