<HEADLINE>
FT  10 MAY 93 / Italian stake in The Independent
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
OFFICIA MECCANICA Cerruti, the Italian manufacturer of printing equipment,
has bought a 2.3 per cent stake in Newspaper Publishing, owner of The
Independent and the Independent on Sunday.
The group bought the stake at 190p a share from Mr John Talbot of Arthur
Andersen, the administrator of Robert Maxwell's private interests. Mr Talbot
still holds another 3.5 per cent stake in Newspaper Publishing that was once
owned by Robert Maxwell.
