THE NATIONAL Lottery planned for the UK could be played every week by most
of the population, with more people watching the live draw every Saturday
night than watch Coronation Street, Raymond Snoddy writes.
A report published today by the GAH consultancy group predicts a significant
impact for the lottery, to be launched next year in aid of 'good causes'.
The report says that in many states and provinces of the US and Canada the
lottery has become the largest contributor to government revenues.
In some countries, such as Norway, the national lottery is the largest
business, it says.
The UK national lottery could become the largest lottery in Europe, ahead of
France and Spain, and could generate sales of between Pounds 2.5bn and
Pounds 6bn. The report says: 'We believe Pounds 4bn to Pounds 4.5bn is an
