Philip Gwyn, a non-executive director of Alumasc, the group that designs and
manufactures products for the brewing and building industries, sold 196,000
shares at 525p to leave him holding about 6 per cent of the ordinary shares.
Last September, four of the directors of Shandwick, the public relations
consultancy group, bought large numbers of shares at prices between 2.75 and
5p. Among them was John Huckle, the finance director, who bought 615,384.
Last week he sold 350,000, at 19.5p.
