<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PRICE, PETER JOHN and STEVE THOMPSON
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The market's appetite for a bid for United Biscuits shows no signs of
abating, with continued talk of a predator emerging over the weekend. Once
again Cadbury Schweppes was being tipped as the chief suspect, although food
manufacturing analysts continued to cast doubts on the speculation. Other
names being mentioned included Associated British Foods and old takeover
favourite Hanson. The UB price zoomed ahead again, closing up 8 to 429p.
